    Add comprehensive MCP server for Obsidian vault interaction
    
    Implements a full-featured Model Context Protocol (MCP) server that provides
    AI assistants with powerful tools to interact with Obsidian vaults.
    
    Features:
    - Vector search using ChromaDB and sentence transformers
    - Regular/fuzzy text search across all notes
    - Complete CRUD operations (create, read, update, delete notes)
    - Folder management
    - Note modification via unified diff format
    - Vault statistics and management
    - OAuth 2.1 authentication with JWT validation
    - Three MCP resources for vault access
    - Two prompt templates for common workflows
    
    Tools implemented:
    1. vector_search - Semantic search using embeddings
    2. text_search - Regex and fuzzy text matching
    3. create_note - Create new markdown notes with frontmatter
    4. create_folder - Create vault directories
    5. read_note - Read note contents and metadata
    6. update_note_diff - Modify notes using diff/patch
    7. delete_note - Safe deletion with trash folder option
    8. list_notes - Browse vault with filtering
    9. get_vault_stats - Comprehensive vault statistics
    10. reindex_vault - Rebuild vector database index
    
    New files:
    - mcp_server.py: Main MCP server implementation (1,000+ lines)
    - MCP_README.md: Comprehensive documentation and usage guide
    
    Configuration updates:
    - requirements.txt: Added MCP SDK, PyJWT, cryptography, httpx
    - example.env: Added OAuth 2.1 configuration options with examples
    
    The server follows MCP best practices and OAuth 2.1 standards for
    secure, production-ready AI agent integration.

